Here $m_{1,6,7}$, $n_1$ and $n_6$ are even, the other five parameters  $n_{2,3,4,5}$ and $n_7$ are odd.
In the 7-parametric family of \cite{MMfam} the three $m$'s were fixed to be $2$,$2$,$\pm 2$.
\begin{eqnarray}
P^{(n_{2,3,4,5})}_X =  \frac{(\bar S\bar T^{n_{2,3,4,5}}S)_{_{{\emptyset},X}}}{S_{_{{\emptyset}, X}}}{\nonumber}\\
K^{(m_{1,6},n_{1,6})}_X = \frac{( S T^{m_{1,6}} S^\dagger \bar T^{n_{1,6}}S)_{_{{\emptyset}, X}}}{S_{_{{\emptyset}, X}}}{\nonumber}\\
\bar K^{(m_7,n_7)}_X = \frac{(\bar S\bar T^{m_7}\bar S \bar T^{n_7}S)_{_{{\emptyset}, X}}}{S_{_{{\emptyset}, X}}}
\label{7parfam}
\end{eqnarray}
